My friend is a regular at this place, even the workers know him, so occasionally we get dragged along. I love the place, but I can't handle 2-3 times a week at any restaurant like him. But it's worth promoting as it's one of the best ramen joints in town. Our usual is the garlic version of the ramen (noodles in broth) or the tsukemen (separate noodles and broth). In my photos are of them - the red one being level 5 spicy which only that friend can handle (I can handle level 4, but then it would be detractive of the taste). The level of customization for the ramen dishes is unreal - noodle size, firmness, spicy level, salt level of the broth, to the myriad of meat and vegetable add-ons, etc. So the price is fine in the beginning, until your eyes get too greedy. Opens at 11:30am, but people quickly start packing in where if you arrive near 12 you have to wait in queue. Parking has only about 5 dedicated stalls, but luckily street parking isn't difficult at that part of the street. Recommended, but if you see some lonely guy hogging a whole table to himself, don't mind him, that's probably my friend.

Yummy ramen place! So glad we tried it here. The restaurant is on the smaller side, but clean and the space is efficiently used. At the entrance, is a tablet to electronically write your name down on a waiting list. We went on a Thursday night and it was full but we didn't have to wait too long for a table. The staff were all nice and friendly. I liked the different choices of ramen broth and that you could customize the salt and heat levels and even the size and firmness of the noodles. We got bowls with the classic tonkotsu broth, the classic shoyu, and a vegetarian broth. They were all good and flavorful. They all came with a soft boiled egg, but it was too undercooked for my liking. The veggie ramen was delicious but a tad too strong in garlic flavor (next time I'll ask for the toasted garlic on the side). We also ordered the corn tempura, gyoza, and the chicken karaage. It was all good. Loved the chicken and corn! The only thing that we didn't like was the time it took for some of the dishes to come out. We also tried the Mac nut sundae and almond pudding for dessert. They weren't anything to write home about and I wouldn't order them again. Overall, the ramen and side dishes were delicious and we will definitely be back.
